<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<task id="070" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r3">
  <metadata>
    <title>Deploy BFF API + SpaarkeAi Code Page to dev environment (end-to-end deploy)</title>
    <phase>Phase G — Deploy + Smoke</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>2</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>060, 061, 062, 063, 065</dependencies>
    <blocks>071, 072, 073, 074</blocks>
    <tags>deploy, dataverse, azure, bff-api, frontend</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Production-style deployment touching shared infrastructure (Azure App Service + Dataverse). Requires real cloud credentials. Per task-execute decision tree, deployment-related tasks run at FULL rigor with deployment-skill safety checks.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>G-deploy</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Single deployment sequence — BFF must land first (frontend's PATCH /tabs + attachments[] endpoints depend on it); SpaarkeAi follows; verification gates the smoke wave.</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Deploy the R3 changes end-to-end to the dev environment in two stages:
    (1) BFF API to Azure App Service via `scripts/Deploy-BffApi.ps1` so the new
    attachments[] endpoint (task 050) + tabs[] endpoint (task 065) are reachable;
    (2) SpaarkeAi Code Page web resource to Dataverse via `scripts/Deploy-SpaarkeAi.ps1`
    so the frontend changes can exercise the new BFF endpoints end-to-end.
    Verify each deployment with its respective health check. Record the deployment
    in `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r3/notes/deploys/{YYYY-MM-DD}-deploy.md`.
    This task is the gate for Phase G smoke testing — no smoke test runs until BOTH
    deploys PASS.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Spaarke deployment operator comfortable with the canonical deploy scripts
    (`scripts/Deploy-BffApi.ps1` for Azure App Service, `scripts/Build-ViteSolutionsDirect.ps1`
    + `scripts/Deploy-SpaarkeAi.ps1` for the Code Page) and the `code-page-deploy` skill.
    Familiar with `az` CLI / PAC CLI authentication. Comfortable reading health-check output
    and rolling back via swap-back if BFF deploy fails post-swap.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Both R3 surfaces are deployed to the dev environment and verified healthy:
    (1) BFF API at `https://spe-api-dev-67e2xz.azurewebsites.net` (default — confirm via script)
    responds OK to `/healthz` and the new `/api/ai/chat/sessions/{id}/tabs` + extended
    `/api/ai/chat/sessions/{id}/messages` (with attachments[]) endpoints respond per ADR-008
    filters. (2) SpaarkeAi web resource `sprk_spaarkeai` is loaded into Dataverse at
    `https://spaarkedev1.crm.dynamics.com` (default — confirm via script) and renders.
    A deploy memo records environment names, target URLs, commit SHA, build/deploy output,
    and health-check evidence. Phase G smoke tasks 071-074 can now run.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      R3 made coordinated frontend + backend changes:
      - Frontend (SpaarkeAi Code Page): PaneHeader, HistoryOverlay, SprkChat toolbar +
        useChatFileAttachment, WorkspacePane LegalWorkspace embed, WorkspacePaneMenu,
        Daily Briefing section consumer, GetStartedCardsWidget, wizard dispatchers,
        AssignWork launcher, write-through to /tabs.
      - Backend (Sprk.Bff.Api): ChatEndpoints extended with `attachments[]` on POST
        messages (task 050) and new PATCH/GET `/sessions/{id}/tabs` (task 065).

      Wave 5 verification gates all PASSED (auth audit CLEAN, dark-mode CLEAN, backwards-compat
      PASS, bundle-size Option 1 accepted with NFR-12 deviation documented). Task 065 closed
      the NFR-09 tab-persistence gap. All blocking work is on git (PR #296, latest commits
      pushed to origin). The codebase compiles cleanly for both targets.

      The two halves MUST be deployed together because the frontend will fail to use
      attachments + tab persistence if it hits the OLD BFF (the new endpoints return 404).
      Deploy order: BFF first (existing clients work unchanged), then SpaarkeAi (new clients
      can use the new endpoints).
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>scripts/Deploy-BffApi.ps1</file>
      <file>scripts/Deploy-SpaarkeAi.ps1</file>
      <file>scripts/Build-ViteSolutionsDirect.ps1</file>
      <file>scripts/Test-Deployment.ps1</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Sprk.Bff.Api.csproj</file>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/package.json</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="project">All Phase F audits (060, 061, 062, 063) MUST be COMPLETE with PASS/CLEAN verdicts. Task 065 (NFR-09 fix) MUST be COMPLETE. Verify by reading each verification memo + checking TASK-INDEX before invoking deployment.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Use the canonical scripts (`Deploy-BffApi.ps1`, `Build-ViteSolutionsDirect.ps1`, `Deploy-SpaarkeAi.ps1`, `Test-Deployment.ps1`). Do not invent ad-hoc deploy invocations.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-026">SpaarkeAi is a full-page Code Page (NOT PCF). Use `code-page-deploy` skill semantics, not `pcf-deploy`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-028">No auth code or token paths are exercised by deployment scripts themselves; deployment auth uses `az login` / PAC CLI / service principal per environment standard. Verify `az account show` succeeds before running Deploy-BffApi.ps1.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Default environment is DEV. If the user has not explicitly requested a different environment, do NOT deploy to staging or production. Confirm DEV target via script defaults before running.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Deploy order is REQUIRED: BFF first, then SpaarkeAi. Reason: frontend write-through to /tabs will silently fail until the BFF endpoint exists. Reverse order leaves the frontend broken between deploys.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Capture deployment evidence in `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r3/notes/deploys/{YYYY-MM-DD}-deploy.md` — date in filename, both environments + commit SHA + timestamps + health-check output in body.</constraint>
  </constraints>

