  <steps>
    <step order="1" name="Verify Phase F + task 065 gates">
      Read each Phase F verification memo + confirm task 065 status in TASK-INDEX:
      - `notes/audit-auth-2026-05-20.md` — verdict: CLEAN
      - `notes/bundle-size-verification.md` — Option 1 accepted
      - `notes/dark-mode-audit.md` — verdict: CLEAN
      - `notes/backwards-compat-verification.md` — verdict: PASS (with NFR-09 closed by 065)
      - `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md` row 065 — ✅
      If any is missing or FAIL/regressed, STOP and report — do not deploy.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Confirm Azure + Dataverse auth + capture commit SHA">
      - Run `az account show` — verify subscription is selected (should be the DEV
        subscription per `Deploy-BffApi.ps1` defaults).
      - Optionally `pac auth list` to verify Dataverse auth profile (Deploy-SpaarkeAi.ps1
        uses `az` for Dataverse token — verify access scope works).
      - Run `git rev-parse HEAD` and record the deployment commit SHA.
      - Read script defaults to confirm target URLs:
        • BFF: `spe-api-dev-67e2xz.azurewebsites.net` (in `spe-infrastructure-westus2`)
        • Dataverse: `https://spaarkedev1.crm.dynamics.com`
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Build BFF in Release mode">
      Confirm `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/ --configuration Release` succeeds
      (Deploy-BffApi.ps1 does this internally — verify or run separately to surface errors
      early). 0 errors required.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Deploy BFF API to dev App Service">
      Run `scripts/Deploy-BffApi.ps1` (no parameters — defaults to dev env, direct deploy,
      no slot). Capture all output including:
      - Build summary
      - Zip package size
      - Deploy result
      - `/healthz` verification result (should be 200 OK)
      If `/healthz` fails, STOP and report. Do NOT proceed to SpaarkeAi deploy until BFF
      is healthy.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Verify new BFF endpoints respond" optional="true">
      Optional sanity check against the deployed BFF:
      - `GET /healthz` → 200 OK (already verified in step 4)
      - `GET /api/ai/chat/sessions/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000/tabs` → 401 (no auth)
        or 404 (auth handled, session-not-found) — either confirms the endpoint exists.
      - The full happy-path validation happens in Phase G smoke tasks 071-074.
      Document the response codes captured.
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Build SpaarkeAi production bundle">
      Run `scripts/Build-ViteSolutionsDirect.ps1` for SpaarkeAi
      (or `cd src/solutions/SpaarkeAi && npm run build`). Verify build succeeds with
      zero TypeScript errors. Capture bundle gzip size (expected ~798 KB per Phase F
      task 061; document any drift).
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Deploy SpaarkeAi to Dataverse">
      Run `scripts/Deploy-SpaarkeAi.ps1` (no parameters — defaults to spaarkedev1).
      Capture all output:
      - Web resource update result (sprk_spaarkeai)
      - Solution version (if applicable)
      - Publish customizations result
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Verify SpaarkeAi deployment">
      Run `scripts/Test-Deployment.ps1` against the target Dataverse environment.
      Capture verification output. Verify deployment is reported as healthy.
    </step>
    <step order="9" name="Record deploy memo">
      Create `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r3/notes/deploys/{YYYY-MM-DD}-deploy.md`
      with sections:
      - Header: date, commit SHA, environments (BFF + Dataverse)
      - BFF deploy: target URL, build summary, deploy output tail, /healthz status,
        new-endpoint sanity-check codes
      - SpaarkeAi deploy: target URL, build bundle size (gzip), deploy output tail,
        Test-Deployment.ps1 verdict
      - Smoke readiness: confirm both deploys healthy + Phase G smoke 071-074 unblocked
      Mark this task COMPLETE only after the memo exists.
    </step>
    <step order="10" name="Update task status + TASK-INDEX">
      Update task 070 POML status → completed. Update TASK-INDEX row 070 → ✅.
    </step>
  </steps>

