  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">All four Phase F verification memos (060, 061, 062, 063) PLUS task 065 status confirmed before deploy.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`az account show` confirmed correct subscription before BFF deploy.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">BFF Release build succeeded (0 errors).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`scripts/Deploy-BffApi.ps1` ran against dev App Service and `/healthz` returned 200 OK after deploy.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">New BFF endpoints respond with auth/404 codes (proving they exist), not 405/MethodNotAllowed (proving they don't).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">SpaarkeAi vite build succeeded with zero errors.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`scripts/Deploy-SpaarkeAi.ps1` ran against dev Dataverse and reported success.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`scripts/Test-Deployment.ps1` reports the deployment as healthy.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Deploy memo records both deploys, commit SHA, timestamps, and verifies Phase G smoke is unblocked.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    Why deploy ORDER is BFF-first then SpaarkeAi-second: frontend write-through to
    PATCH /tabs (task 065) and POST messages with attachments[] (task 026 wiring) will
    silently fail until the BFF endpoints exist. Pre-task-026 clients sending the
    `attachments` field were silently dropped by the old BFF DTO; post-task-026 clients
    will SEND attachments but the agent won't use them unless task 050's DTO has landed.
    Deploying BFF first ensures both old + new client builds work correctly.

    Why DEV environment: this is the project's first integration deployment. Phase G smoke
    tasks (071-074) need a real Power Apps host to verify FR-02..FR-22 acceptance criteria
    + NFR timings. Staging/production deploys are typically a separate decision after smoke
    passes (and would use `Deploy-BffApi.ps1 -UseSlotDeploy` for zero-downtime).

    BFF deploy can take 5-10 minutes (build + zip + upload + slot warm-up + health check).
    SpaarkeAi deploy is faster (1-2 minutes — single web resource).

    Rollback plan: if BFF deploy fails post-swap, the script auto-rolls back via swap-back
    (RollbackOnFailure default $true). If SpaarkeAi deploy fails, the previous web resource
    version remains in Dataverse — re-import the previous solution if needed.

    Phase H wrap-up (task 090) will document this deploy in the final release notes.
  </notes>

  <execution>
    This task MUST be executed via the `task-execute` skill from `.claude/skills/task-execute/SKILL.md`.
    The deployment itself is orchestrated via the `code-page-deploy` skill (for SpaarkeAi)
    and the standard `Deploy-BffApi.ps1` script (for BFF — no dedicated skill, the script
    is canonical). Do not bypass either path.
  </execution>
</task>
